{"article_id":"JZr8kuhuxTfmF7Gb","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The British prime minister announced Friday","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that she plans to resign ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"after trying","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"- and failing -","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"to steer the United Kingdom through its divorce with the European Union .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"While this brings a close to her beleaguered premiership ,","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"it adds even more chaos to UK politics","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"as the country tries to finalize its exit from the EU .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"May will not leave office immediately .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"She will step aside as leader of the Conservative Party on June 7 ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"which will trigger a leadership contest","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"to replace her on June 10 .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"But she will stay on as prime minister","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"until her successor is selected ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"at which point that person will become the prime minister","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"without the need for a general election .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"A new prime minister was \" in the best interests of the country , \"","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"May said in a statement in front of London ' s 10 Downing Street .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"\" It is and always will remain a matter of deep regret to me","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"that I have not been able to deliver Brexit . \"","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"After calling on ministers to compromise on Brexit issues in the weeks ahead ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"she concluded her address","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"while fighting back tears .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"\" I will shortly leave the job","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"that has been the honor of my life","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"to hold ...","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"I do so with no ill will","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"but with enormous and enduring gratitude","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to have had the opportunity","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"to serve the country","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"I love . \"","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"May will step down amid intensifying pressure from Conservative members of Parliament ,","depth":4},{"id":32,"text":"many of whom have been agitating for her to leave office","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"after her failure","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"to deliver a Brexit deal","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"that could satisfy her party .","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"May has served as prime minister for nearly three years ,","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"ascending to leadership shortly after the 2016 Brexit referendum and the resignation of then-Prime Minister David Cameron .","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"When she took over ,","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"May vowed to deliver Brexit","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"- though what that meant in practical terms ended up being far more complicated .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"The only thing surprising about May ' s resignation is that it took this long","depth":3},{"id":42,"text":"The countdown to May ' s departure began the moment","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"she brought back the Brexit deal","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"negotiated with the EU late last year ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"which both her party and the opposition Labour Party hated .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"When she put the deal before Parliament in January ,","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"MPs defeated it by a stunning margin of 230 votes","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"- the largest defeat for a prime minister in modern British history .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"May failed again on a second attempt in March .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Before making her third attempt ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"she tried a new tactic","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"to get her deal passed :","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"promising to resign","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"if it succeeded .","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"Conservatives","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"who disliked her more","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"than they disliked her deal","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"went along with it ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"but May still couldn ' t muster the votes","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"to pass the plan","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"that would take the UK out of the EU .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"The political stalemate forced her to twice seek an extension of the original March 29 Brexit deadline","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"to avoid a no-deal Brexit .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"That new deadline is now set for October 31 , 2019 , months after the original departure date .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"May weathered this political turmoil","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"as best she could ,","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"but the Brexit delays infuriated the hardcore Brexiteers in her party ,","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"and they vocally , and unashamedly , sought ways","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"to oust her .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"( May survived a no-confidence vote in December 2018 ,","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"and the current rules barred the party from trying again for a full year . )","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Then , last week , May reached a deal with Conservatives MPs :","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"She would set a date for her departure","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"after Parliament approved her Brexit deal","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"( on the fourth try )","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"and the related legislation","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"required","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"to get the UK out of the EU .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"That vote was expected in early June .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"But even that gambit derailed .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"May presented a \" new \" strategy for her Brexit deal this week , in a last-ditch effort","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"to win votes .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"Unfortunately , it didn ' t actually contain much new material .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"And the new compromises","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"it did offer","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"were geared to win over Remainers , most notably with the chance","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"to hold a second Brexit referendum .","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"For the most hardcore Brexiteers in May ' s party , it was an unequivocal betrayal .","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"It also effectively assured","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"May had no chance","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"to persuade Parliament to back her Brexit plan .","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"Under this intensifying pressure","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"- including from her own cabinet ministers -","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"May really had no other choice","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"other than to step down .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"May ' s departure will set off a leadership contest within the Conservative Party","depth":5},{"id":97,"text":"A slew of candidates is already jockeying","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"to take over as Conservative leader","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"and become the next prime minister ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"including Boris Johnson , May ' s former foreign secretary","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"who is staunchly pro-Brexit .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Other former ( and current )","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"members of May ' s cabinet are also expected to compete .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"May managed to survive","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"as long","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"as she did","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"in part because Conservatives couldn ' t agree on anyone better .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"More moderate Conservatives worried","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"a hardcore Brexiteer might steer the UK out of the EU","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"without a deal in place at all ;","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Brexiteers fretted","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"that a more moderate party member might seek an even softer Brexit .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"Brexiteers might have a slight edge in the post-May world ,","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"as they ' re already under pressure from a new Brexit Party","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"that ' s pulling some voters away from the Conservatives .","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"But these divisions within the party aren ' t entirely gone ,","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"and will likely make this leadership contest a bruising battle","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"- one","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"that will consume a very big slice of summer ahead of a fall Brexit deadline .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"In a speech earlier this week , May acknowledged","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"that \" the challenge","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"of taking Brexit from the simplicity of the choice on the ballot paper to the complexity","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"of resetting the country ' s relationship with 27 of its nearest neighbors","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"was always going to be huge . \"","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"That won ' t change ,","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"no matter who the next prime minister is .","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"Whoever takes May ' s place will inherit the still-unresolved Brexit crisis","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"and face the same complex reality","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"she did .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":259,"left":165,"right":258,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":160,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":137,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":134,"right":136,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":131,"right":133,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":133,"left":132,"right":4,"rela